1
00:00:00,500 --> 00:00:01,200
(Previously)
Wait, Gaysorn.

2
00:00:01,500 --> 00:00:02,200
Please listen to me first.

3
00:00:02,201 --> 00:00:03,399
I'm sorry for lying to you.

4
00:00:03,400 --> 00:00:05,899
What do you think of me? A lab rat?

5
00:00:05,900 --> 00:00:07,199
Have you ever even seen
me as a human being?

6
00:00:07,200 --> 00:00:09,899
I already told you that
between me and Gaysorn, it's over!

7
00:00:09,900 --> 00:00:12,299
No! If he wants to know
where his mother is...

8
00:00:12,300 --> 00:00:13,499
he will definitely follow you back!

9
00:00:13,500 --> 00:00:14,999
There are so many documents.
What are you looking for?

10
00:00:15,000 --> 00:00:16,499
Every document related to Pruet.

11
00:00:16,500 --> 00:00:19,700
Your mother was living on the mountain.
Who told her to come down?

12
00:00:20,400 --> 00:00:22,700
Gaysorn, our love is real, Gaysorn.

13
00:00:22,800 --> 00:00:24,600
But right now, I don't love you anymore.

14
00:00:32,200 --> 00:00:37,700
This means someone sent this letter
to trick Bussaba into coming down.

15
00:00:37,800 --> 00:00:38,800
But who?

16
00:01:03,976 --> 00:01:06,000
[Dear Bussaba, I was in a car
accident and I really want to see you.

17
00:01:06,000 --> 00:01:07,000
Please come to Bangkok
as fast as possible.

18
00:01:07,024 --> 00:01:08,070
The person who gave you the letter
will help you get to the city.]

19
00:01:24,385 --> 00:01:25,841
Stop! You can't go.

20
00:01:26,700 --> 00:01:28,761
- Mata.
- Let him go.

21
00:01:31,081 --> 00:01:32,961
If you want to go, then
you can go by yourself.

22
00:01:33,620 --> 00:01:36,001
I won't let you take Gaysorn with you.

23
00:01:36,137 --> 00:01:37,921
I won't let you risk your son's life.

24
00:01:45,497 --> 00:01:46,498
Well…

25
00:01:50,089 --> 00:01:52,161
please take care of him.

26
00:01:53,396 --> 00:01:56,041
Are you going to leave
your son here? Really?

27
00:01:58,297 --> 00:02:00,561
I just went to see Pruek.

28
00:02:00,798 --> 00:02:03,161
He really needs me.

29
00:02:04,281 --> 00:02:06,441
I've been waiting for him

30
00:02:07,519 --> 00:02:10,041
even before Gaysorn was born.

31
00:02:11,281 --> 00:02:12,561
Please, Mata.

32
00:02:14,201 --> 00:02:15,202
Let me go.

33
00:02:37,095 --> 00:02:39,281
I just need to see your dad.

34
00:02:40,349 --> 00:02:42,181
I will be back soon, okay?

35
00:02:42,907 --> 00:02:45,607
Mom, please hurry back.

36
00:02:49,269 --> 00:02:51,327
It's not like I am leaving you.

37
00:02:52,568 --> 00:02:54,794
I am still with you, always.

38
00:03:12,374 --> 00:03:14,375
Please take care of him for me.

39
00:03:18,180 --> 00:03:19,241
Just go. Go!

40
00:04:11,263 --> 00:04:12,264
Bussaba?

41
00:04:20,027 --> 00:04:21,028
Why are you here?

42
00:04:24,502 --> 00:04:25,503
I…

43
00:04:27,681 --> 00:04:29,001
Well, Pruek's condition is so bad

44
00:04:30,390 --> 00:04:31,814
he can barely move.

45
00:04:33,644 --> 00:04:36,561
If it wasn't me, then who would be here?

46
00:04:38,064 --> 00:04:39,065
But…

47
00:04:40,356 --> 00:04:41,357
you…

48
00:04:42,170 --> 00:04:43,247
you make the perfumes.

49
00:04:48,186 --> 00:04:49,187
I understand why

50
00:04:50,010 --> 00:04:51,291
you wouldn't trust me.

51
00:04:55,212 --> 00:04:57,681
It's fine if you don't trust me,

52
00:04:58,353 --> 00:04:59,713
you don't have to go back with me.

53
00:05:03,082 --> 00:05:04,083
Wait.

54
00:05:08,012 --> 00:05:09,013
How…

55
00:05:09,980 --> 00:05:11,401
how is he?

56
00:05:15,202 --> 00:05:16,682
Your husband's condition is very bad.

57
00:05:19,161 --> 00:05:20,751
If you don't come back with me now,

58
00:05:22,831 --> 00:05:24,671
perhaps you wouldn't
be able to see him again.

59
00:07:21,100 --> 00:07:25,100
"Flower Boy"
(Episode 7)

60
00:07:32,001 --> 00:07:34,681
Your uncle called me to
bring Gaysorn's scent project back.

61
00:07:34,817 --> 00:07:35,818
What is going on?

62
00:07:37,655 --> 00:07:39,381
He ordered me to bring Gaysorn back.

63
00:07:41,543 --> 00:07:42,903
What is your plan to get him back?

64
00:07:45,017 --> 00:07:47,177
He said that if Gaysorn heard about
where his mom was,

65
00:07:47,796 --> 00:07:48,797
he would come back.

66
00:07:50,308 --> 00:07:51,309
Huh?

67
00:07:51,641 --> 00:07:53,042
- It means that…
- That's right.

68
00:07:55,481 --> 00:07:57,601
My uncle has known about his mom
since the beginning.

69
00:08:15,953 --> 00:08:18,401
What are you going to do?
Are you going to tell Gaysorn?

70
00:08:21,415 --> 00:08:22,441
I think this is strange.

71
00:08:23,692 --> 00:08:24,721
Let me think about it.

72
00:08:30,111 --> 00:08:31,721
I don't want to hurt him anymore.

73
00:09:17,399 --> 00:09:18,400
Does it smell good?

74
00:09:26,583 --> 00:09:27,584
Is it good?

75
00:09:34,084 --> 00:09:35,281
Your cheek smells better.

76
00:11:39,809 --> 00:11:43,001
So you're going to take Gaysorn
and his Mudan clan back to your place?

77
00:11:44,295 --> 00:11:45,296
Yup.

78
00:11:46,908 --> 00:11:48,161
You're so dedicated,

79
00:11:49,231 --> 00:11:50,391
are you aimimg for something?

80
00:11:51,841 --> 00:11:54,442
Who would do that? He
is looking for his mom.

81
00:11:54,881 --> 00:11:55,882
Right,

82
00:11:56,548 --> 00:11:57,921
I wish your dream comes true.

83
00:12:01,961 --> 00:12:03,121
I gotta go, Gaysorn is here.

84
00:12:03,733 --> 00:12:04,734
Sure.

85
00:12:09,284 --> 00:12:10,285
Mata,

86
00:12:10,751 --> 00:12:12,324
this is Mekin.

87
00:12:13,412 --> 00:12:14,413
He is very nice to me.

88
00:12:16,527 --> 00:12:17,921
This is Mata, she is my aunt.

89
00:12:18,528 --> 00:12:19,529
Hello.

90
00:12:21,156 --> 00:12:23,401
This is my brother, Tawan.

91
00:12:28,828 --> 00:12:29,829
Can we go now?

92
00:12:31,185 --> 00:12:33,601
This way, I've prepared a van for you.

93
00:12:34,007 --> 00:12:35,008
Let's go.

94
00:12:54,993 --> 00:12:55,994
Hello?

95
00:12:56,847 --> 00:12:58,247
I'm waiting in front of your house.

96
00:12:58,541 --> 00:12:59,542
Come out to see me.

97
00:13:01,342 --> 00:13:02,343
Gaysorn?

98
00:13:06,761 --> 00:13:07,762
Gaysorn.

99
00:13:21,841 --> 00:13:23,241
I need to talk to you.

100
00:13:25,816 --> 00:13:27,025
You can come inside.

101
00:13:27,331 --> 00:13:29,623
No need. You can talk here.

102
00:13:30,631 --> 00:13:33,121
How could you ask him to
come inside of the house?

103
00:13:34,537 --> 00:13:36,321
Besides using him,

104
00:13:37,193 --> 00:13:38,921
have you realized what you have done?

105
00:13:43,689 --> 00:13:45,711
Fire! Fire! Hurry up!

106
00:13:47,073 --> 00:13:48,074
How is it?

107
00:13:48,281 --> 00:13:51,282
He ran away with Gaysorn!
He took Gaysorn with him!

108
00:13:54,662 --> 00:13:56,182
I didn't know it'd turn out like that.

109
00:13:57,553 --> 00:13:59,761
I didn't mean to burn down your village.

110
00:14:00,881 --> 00:14:02,041
You need to pay.

111
00:14:03,793 --> 00:14:05,201
It's water under the bridge.

112
00:14:06,589 --> 00:14:08,090
There is nothing we can do.

113
00:14:12,660 --> 00:14:13,761
I'm really sorry.

114
00:14:14,833 --> 00:14:16,993
If you need me to pay in
any way, please let me know.

115
00:14:24,407 --> 00:14:26,131
This is the letter that someone sent to Mom

116
00:14:26,876 --> 00:14:28,841
after Dad had been dead for four years.

117
00:14:30,521 --> 00:14:32,281
It told her to leave
the village to see Dad.

118
00:14:37,113 --> 00:14:38,381
Can you find out who did this?

119
00:14:55,444 --> 00:14:56,445
What's the matter?

120
00:14:59,972 --> 00:15:00,973
Nothing.

121
00:15:03,783 --> 00:15:06,561
I can keep this letter for you
and I will search more about it.

122
00:15:09,268 --> 00:15:10,631
You can trust me.

123
00:15:24,319 --> 00:15:26,721
Where are you staying?

124
00:15:27,785 --> 00:15:30,201
You can stay here so we can talk easily.

125
00:15:30,868 --> 00:15:31,981
We're staying at Mekin's place.

126
00:15:34,353 --> 00:15:35,681
You have my phone number

127
00:15:37,081 --> 00:15:38,801
you can call me when there is any progress.

128
00:15:45,564 --> 00:15:46,565
Gaysorn.

129
00:15:56,391 --> 00:15:57,392
I'm glad

130
00:15:58,177 --> 00:15:59,281
that you still trust me.

131
00:16:04,492 --> 00:16:05,681
I just don't have a choice.

132
00:16:07,479 --> 00:16:08,480
Gaysorn,

133
00:16:12,033 --> 00:16:13,034
no matter what.

134
00:16:15,500 --> 00:16:16,501
I'm still glad

135
00:16:18,572 --> 00:16:19,573
that I got to see you.

136
00:16:25,591 --> 00:16:26,592
I missed you.

137
00:16:55,252 --> 00:16:56,451
I really missed you.

138
00:17:22,196 --> 00:17:23,197
Let's get going.

139
00:17:27,273 --> 00:17:28,274
Gaysorn?

140
00:17:29,684 --> 00:17:31,081
Stop hurting him already.

141
00:17:59,631 --> 00:18:01,831
If you need to hold back your feelings
when seeing him,

142
00:18:02,740 --> 00:18:04,381
I don't think you should see him anymore.

143
00:18:05,455 --> 00:18:06,456
Tawan.

144
00:18:06,959 --> 00:18:08,281
Did I say something wrong, Mata?

145
00:18:10,692 --> 00:18:12,001
What are you going to do next?

146
00:18:12,559 --> 00:18:14,319
Are we just going to wait
for him like this?

147
00:18:18,549 --> 00:18:20,301
Is there anybody or anything

148
00:18:20,724 --> 00:18:24,281
that can lead us to what
happened 20 years ago?

149
00:18:33,103 --> 00:18:34,761
Yes, I think so.

150
00:18:41,156 --> 00:18:42,157
Hello?

151
00:18:42,601 --> 00:18:43,602
Mekin,

152
00:18:44,345 --> 00:18:46,161
can you tell your driver

153
00:18:47,599 --> 00:18:48,761
to take us somewhere?

154
00:19:08,463 --> 00:19:10,041
This is Mom and Dad's old house.

155
00:19:10,887 --> 00:19:12,681
It has been abandoned for years.

156
00:19:24,291 --> 00:19:25,521
Why are we here?

157
00:19:44,351 --> 00:19:45,681
You need to talk to me?

158
00:19:47,802 --> 00:19:48,803
I want to ask you

159
00:19:49,431 --> 00:19:50,841
about Bussaba, Gaysorn's mother.

160
00:19:53,143 --> 00:19:54,781
How did you know where she was?

161
00:20:01,292 --> 00:20:02,532
You need to bring Gaysorn to me

162
00:20:04,263 --> 00:20:05,264
and we can talk.

163
00:20:05,436 --> 00:20:06,561
You need to tell me first.

164
00:20:06,921 --> 00:20:08,041
You don't trust me?

165
00:20:09,039 --> 00:20:10,040
Of course, I trust you.

166
00:20:11,001 --> 00:20:12,281
I believe that you know.

167
00:20:13,327 --> 00:20:16,681
You were the one who sent the letter,
tricking Bussaba to leave the mountains.

168
00:20:17,081 --> 00:20:18,082
Am I right?

169
00:20:20,839 --> 00:20:22,881
What are you talking about? What letter?

170
00:20:25,722 --> 00:20:26,723
This letter.

171
00:20:31,092 --> 00:20:33,561
It was sent after Pruek
died four years earlier.

172
00:20:34,692 --> 00:20:36,292
Pruek couldn't send the letter for sure.

173
00:20:37,988 --> 00:20:39,381
Who else could it be?

174
00:20:40,412 --> 00:20:41,881
Didn't you see the letter head?

175
00:20:42,413 --> 00:20:44,133
It could have only come
from the executive level. only.

176
00:20:59,501 --> 00:21:00,881
Is it because of the letter head?

177
00:21:03,177 --> 00:21:05,081
That's why you believed it was me?

178
00:21:27,903 --> 00:21:28,904
Mata,

179
00:21:30,265 --> 00:21:31,745
I remember that back in Mudan village

180
00:21:32,209 --> 00:21:33,801
you can talk to the dead.

181
00:21:35,692 --> 00:21:37,381
I'd like you to talk to Dad.

182
00:21:38,561 --> 00:21:39,862
I want to know where Mom is.

183
00:21:42,641 --> 00:21:43,642
Gaysorn,

184
00:21:44,996 --> 00:21:47,521
if you want Mata to talk to the dead,

185
00:21:48,452 --> 00:21:50,012
we have to use that person's belongings

186
00:21:50,287 --> 00:21:51,641
so Mata can start the ritual.

187
00:21:52,881 --> 00:21:53,882
I have one.

188
00:21:57,996 --> 00:21:59,841
This is his photo.

189
00:22:07,113 --> 00:22:08,481
I found it at home.

190
00:22:09,581 --> 00:22:10,582
Gaysorn.

191
00:22:12,401 --> 00:22:13,641
Normally,

192
00:22:15,116 --> 00:22:16,681
when Mudan people

193
00:22:18,183 --> 00:22:19,401
pass away,

194
00:22:20,833 --> 00:22:21,834
their souls

195
00:22:23,231 --> 00:22:26,481
will protect their children for a while.

196
00:22:28,321 --> 00:22:31,041
That's why I could communicate to them.

197
00:22:32,385 --> 00:22:33,721
But your dad

198
00:22:35,233 --> 00:22:36,481
wasn't from Mudan.

199
00:22:40,186 --> 00:22:41,187
Earlier,

200
00:22:41,745 --> 00:22:43,401
I walked through the house

201
00:22:44,512 --> 00:22:46,401
and I felt nothing.

202
00:22:49,855 --> 00:22:51,481
It's been a while.

203
00:22:53,953 --> 00:22:54,981
I don't think your dad

204
00:22:56,097 --> 00:22:57,381
can come to me.

205
00:23:00,487 --> 00:23:01,788
More importantly,

206
00:23:02,455 --> 00:23:03,881
this is not our place,

207
00:23:05,759 --> 00:23:08,841
I'm not sure if I can communicate to him.

208
00:24:01,788 --> 00:24:03,281
Why are there flowers here?

209
00:24:05,001 --> 00:24:06,002
Watch out!

210
00:24:08,781 --> 00:24:09,782
I'm fine.

211
00:24:21,124 --> 00:24:23,381
I think the ground is uneven here.

212
00:24:24,921 --> 00:24:26,001
There must be something below.

213
00:24:26,841 --> 00:24:27,842
Gaysorn,

214
00:24:28,161 --> 00:24:29,981
Tawan, find something to dig with. Hurry.

215
00:24:41,020 --> 00:24:42,021
Gaysorn.

216
00:25:27,268 --> 00:25:30,937
These are documents from your dad's office.

217
00:25:55,009 --> 00:25:57,561
I wasn't the only one
using the letter head paper.

218
00:26:02,052 --> 00:26:03,153
What do you mean?

219
00:26:11,929 --> 00:26:13,321
Think about it.

220
00:26:15,700 --> 00:26:16,701
Who

221
00:26:18,097 --> 00:26:19,681
was obsessed with Mudan's scent?

222
00:26:24,731 --> 00:26:25,732
Do you mean that

223
00:26:27,161 --> 00:26:28,251
Gaysorn's mom

224
00:26:29,823 --> 00:26:31,024
went to see my dad?

225
00:26:38,457 --> 00:26:40,201
What happened to her? Where is she?

226
00:26:46,588 --> 00:26:48,589
What you want to find out

227
00:26:50,340 --> 00:26:53,036
is right here, in the
basement of this house.

228
00:27:16,897 --> 00:27:18,481
What is in the basement?

229
00:27:20,401 --> 00:27:21,481
You can go and have a look.

230
00:28:09,597 --> 00:28:10,598
What is it?

231
00:28:14,721 --> 00:28:15,781
Your dad

232
00:28:16,710 --> 00:28:18,601
really wanted Mudan's scent so bad.

233
00:28:22,644 --> 00:28:24,481
So he kept Bussaba in here.

234
00:28:59,001 --> 00:29:01,002
[16 Years Ago]

235
00:29:09,857 --> 00:29:11,381
We use the heat to make her sweat

236
00:29:12,252 --> 00:29:13,892
and we will extract the scent from her sweat.

237
00:30:14,015 --> 00:30:15,016
It doesn't smell good.

238
00:30:22,144 --> 00:30:23,801
Why didn't it smell good?

239
00:30:28,641 --> 00:30:30,041
Your dad refused to stop.

240
00:30:30,481 --> 00:30:32,601
He tried every way possible

241
00:30:33,001 --> 00:30:35,381
to extract Bussaba's scent.

242
00:30:35,921 --> 00:30:38,721
He used a cloth to
collect the scent from her skin.

243
00:30:55,516 --> 00:30:57,007
No matter how hard he tried,

244
00:30:58,181 --> 00:30:59,601
he still couldn't get her scent.

245
00:31:15,073 --> 00:31:17,881
Why doesn't the perfume extracted
from your scent smell good?

246
00:31:18,881 --> 00:31:19,882
I already told you.

247
00:31:20,551 --> 00:31:22,241
My scent is gone.

248
00:31:22,881 --> 00:31:23,982
I have a child.

249
00:31:24,581 --> 00:31:25,841
Don't lie to me.

250
00:31:30,121 --> 00:31:31,381
I didn't lie to you.

251
00:31:32,500 --> 00:31:33,921
Women from Mudan

252
00:31:34,381 --> 00:31:36,382
will lose her scent once they have babies.

253
00:31:38,161 --> 00:31:39,381
That's the way it is.

254
00:31:40,831 --> 00:31:42,731
Then you need to stay right here

255
00:31:43,635 --> 00:31:45,761
until we find the way to get your scent.

256
00:32:32,559 --> 00:32:35,161
Damn it! Why can't it be scented?

257
00:33:26,772 --> 00:33:27,773
Tell me.

258
00:33:28,655 --> 00:33:30,441
How can I get the scent out of you?

259
00:33:31,647 --> 00:33:32,648
I've told you

260
00:33:33,017 --> 00:33:34,281
that you won't get it.

261
00:33:34,701 --> 00:33:36,402
Don't lie to me.

262
00:33:38,244 --> 00:33:41,041
Tell me. Tell me now!

263
00:33:41,521 --> 00:33:43,322
What is the secret? Tell me.

264
00:33:43,671 --> 00:33:44,801
- Anurak?
- Tell me.

265
00:33:45,072 --> 00:33:47,081
Hey!

266
00:33:50,841 --> 00:33:52,207
What have you done?

267
00:34:05,793 --> 00:34:07,241
Your dad lost it completely.

268
00:34:08,316 --> 00:34:09,601
And he hurt that woman.

269
00:34:11,921 --> 00:34:13,445
I tried to save her

270
00:34:15,988 --> 00:34:17,041
but I was too late.

271
00:34:18,989 --> 00:34:20,381
Later, I found out

272
00:34:21,801 --> 00:34:22,981
that Bussaba

273
00:34:25,297 --> 00:34:26,298
was already dead.

274
00:34:27,991 --> 00:34:28,992
Dead?

275
00:34:30,668 --> 00:34:31,681
Where was her body?

276
00:34:32,668 --> 00:34:34,761
- Where was her body?
- I destroyed it all.

277
00:34:36,599 --> 00:34:38,121
What the hell did you do?

278
00:34:38,593 --> 00:34:40,001
What did you do?

279
00:34:41,052 --> 00:34:42,581
What did you expect me to do?

280
00:34:42,889 --> 00:34:44,721
Your dad is my brother

281
00:34:44,781 --> 00:34:46,261
and I won't let him go to jail.

282
00:34:48,097 --> 00:34:51,201
I had to do what was
the best for our family.

283
00:35:38,508 --> 00:35:40,401
It's been more than 10 years,

284
00:35:42,161 --> 00:35:44,001
why did you bring up the evidence?

285
00:35:44,647 --> 00:35:46,681
Why did you dig up the past for?

286
00:35:47,756 --> 00:35:49,201
Think about it.

287
00:35:50,199 --> 00:35:51,759
The most guilty person in the situation

288
00:35:52,532 --> 00:35:53,841
was your dad.

289
00:35:56,895 --> 00:35:59,041
You want to put your dad in jail?

290
00:36:31,428 --> 00:36:32,429
Gaysorn,

291
00:36:33,353 --> 00:36:36,081
I won't stop looking for your mom.

292
00:36:37,281 --> 00:36:40,801
I don't care how long
it takes, I will find her.

293
00:36:44,098 --> 00:36:45,099
Thank you.

294
00:36:49,734 --> 00:36:52,001
No matter what, we will find your mom.

295
00:38:03,257 --> 00:38:04,258
Tawan, what is it?

296
00:39:13,401 --> 00:39:15,681
I just need to see your dad.

297
00:39:16,161 --> 00:39:17,521
I will be back soon, okay?

298
00:39:42,764 --> 00:39:45,561
Mom, please hurry back.

299
00:39:47,377 --> 00:39:49,178
Mom! Mom!

300
00:40:30,161 --> 00:40:32,201
Mom!

301
00:42:24,439 --> 00:42:25,761
This is a homicide.

302
00:42:38,777 --> 00:42:39,778
Are you okay?

303
00:42:42,615 --> 00:42:44,681
I want them to pay for
what they did to Mom.

304
00:42:54,511 --> 00:42:55,671
I'm sorry for saying this but

305
00:42:57,031 --> 00:42:58,601
it happened aged ago.

306
00:42:58,887 --> 00:43:00,601
It's been 15-16 years already.

307
00:43:02,385 --> 00:43:05,081
Moreover, there are only bones

308
00:43:05,271 --> 00:43:06,281
left in this hole.

309
00:43:07,278 --> 00:43:09,507
We barely have anything
that links back to the criminals.

310
00:43:09,964 --> 00:43:10,981
What about the letter?

311
00:43:12,001 --> 00:43:14,481
The person who wrote the letter to
fool his mom was the bad guy.

312
00:43:26,385 --> 00:43:27,386
Kusuma!

313
00:44:09,909 --> 00:44:10,910
Dad?

314
00:44:15,172 --> 00:44:17,161
I know about Bussaba.

315
00:44:24,241 --> 00:44:25,802
Why did you do that?

316
00:44:31,153 --> 00:44:32,801
I don't know what to tell Gaysorn

317
00:44:36,375 --> 00:44:37,655
that a person who killed his mom

318
00:44:39,281 --> 00:44:40,282
was you.

319
00:44:47,633 --> 00:44:49,281
I don't want you to be in jail.

320
00:44:53,615 --> 00:44:55,881
But I shouldn't be the
one who makes the decision,

321
00:44:59,301 --> 00:45:01,352
Gaysorn should do it.

322
00:45:09,561 --> 00:45:10,562
I love you

323
00:45:13,519 --> 00:45:15,001
and I love him, too.

324
00:45:19,320 --> 00:45:21,081
I don't want to lie to him anymore.

325
00:45:27,281 --> 00:45:28,541
Please tell me.

326
00:45:29,641 --> 00:45:31,001
Tell me what to do.

327
00:45:56,527 --> 00:45:58,361
Dad! Dad!

328
00:45:58,991 --> 00:46:01,281
Dad! Dad!

329
00:46:01,321 --> 00:46:02,521
Dad! Dad!

330
00:46:02,922 --> 00:46:04,841
Dad! Dad!

331
00:46:06,041 --> 00:46:07,801
Dad! Dad!

332
00:46:10,399 --> 00:46:11,400
Dad!

333
00:46:22,953 --> 00:46:23,954
Dad!

334
00:46:24,129 --> 00:46:25,130
Dad! Dad!

335
00:46:31,075 --> 00:46:32,076
Anurak!

336
00:46:33,959 --> 00:46:34,960
Scent,

337
00:46:36,055 --> 00:46:38,161
what did you do to upset your dad?

338
00:46:38,909 --> 00:46:40,121
We'll talk later.

339
00:46:41,559 --> 00:46:42,560
Dad!

340
00:46:43,232 --> 00:46:44,758
Dad! Dad!

341
00:47:00,977 --> 00:47:02,615
Dad! Dad!

342
00:47:03,857 --> 00:47:05,481
I'm taking you to the hospital.

343
00:47:10,316 --> 00:47:11,401
What are you trying to say?

344
00:47:15,401 --> 00:47:16,402
I…

345
00:47:18,087 --> 00:47:19,088
I?

346
00:47:22,800 --> 00:47:23,800
I...

347
00:47:25,981 --> 00:47:26,982
didn't…

348
00:47:29,441 --> 00:47:30,442
do it.

349
00:47:34,044 --> 00:47:35,045
You didn't do it?

350
00:47:37,721 --> 00:47:39,449
You're telling me that you didn't do it?

351
00:47:45,847 --> 00:47:47,381
Dad! Dad!

352
00:48:18,972 --> 00:48:19,973
Smells so nice.

353
00:48:24,983 --> 00:48:25,984
There you go, I'm done.

354
00:48:38,013 --> 00:48:40,199
It's a scented sachet. It's cute.

355
00:48:40,737 --> 00:48:41,738
Do you want one?

356
00:48:43,581 --> 00:48:46,082
You can pick your scent
and I'll draw you for free.

357
00:48:47,740 --> 00:48:48,741
What do you say?

358
00:48:50,561 --> 00:48:52,841
She will draw your face on the sachet.

359
00:48:55,324 --> 00:48:56,325
I want one.

360
00:49:03,531 --> 00:49:04,761
Pick your scent, please.

361
00:49:14,102 --> 00:49:15,103
I'll pick this one.

362
00:49:15,334 --> 00:49:16,335
Sure.

363
00:49:17,561 --> 00:49:18,562
Well,

364
00:49:19,961 --> 00:49:20,962
I need one too.

365
00:49:21,364 --> 00:49:22,365
Alright.

366
00:49:34,961 --> 00:49:35,962
Just a second.

367
00:49:50,396 --> 00:49:51,721
This is more like you.

368
00:49:58,764 --> 00:50:02,121
Can you draw him with
butterflies on his body?

369
00:50:02,765 --> 00:50:03,766
Sure, I can.

370
00:50:35,519 --> 00:50:37,641
Wow! So cute.

371
00:50:45,881 --> 00:50:47,761
I will keep your face with me

372
00:50:49,481 --> 00:50:51,441
and you can keep one with mine.

373
00:51:06,631 --> 00:51:07,632
Smells so nice.

374
00:51:15,473 --> 00:51:16,474
Is it good?

375
00:51:17,303 --> 00:51:18,504
Yes, so nice.

376
00:51:28,477 --> 00:51:30,064
(Next Episode) This means
the person who wrote the

377
00:51:30,088 --> 00:51:31,676
letter must have known
Gaysorn's mother very well.

378
00:51:31,700 --> 00:51:33,199
And back then,
how many people would have known about it?

379
00:51:33,200 --> 00:51:34,800
Scent's father and uncle.

380
00:51:39,000 --> 00:51:40,000
Dad...

381
00:51:41,200 --> 00:51:43,280
Scent asked me to pick up
his things from the house.

382
00:51:47,000 --> 00:51:48,199
Go back to the Mudan tribe.

383
00:51:48,200 --> 00:51:51,400
This place is too cruel.
It's not suitable for you.

384
00:51:51,500 --> 00:51:55,700
And I... am not worthy
of you. I'm sorry.

385
00:51:59,200 --> 00:52:00,400
Scent...

